{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017716,"pPcc":"SAT#H","questionId":"a91a2b75","skill_cd":"H.B.","score_band_range_cd":4,"skill_desc":"Linear functions","createDate":1755117017716,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Algebra","ibn":"","external_id":"0beb2470-2acd-4279-917c-0e0172947d97","primary_class_cd":"H","uId":"93690e17-944e-4073-af0e-cd99e9404ea4","difficulty":"M"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"spr","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The function <math alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi>\n</math> is defined by <math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals negative 9 x plus 9\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>9</mn></mrow></math>. What is the <math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math>-coordinate of the <math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math>-intercept of the graph of <math alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> in the <math alttext=\"x y\"><mrow>\n\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t<mi>y</mi>\n</mrow>\n</math>-plane?</p>","keys":["9"],"rationale":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn></math>. The <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;in the <em>xy</em>-plane is the point where the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> crosses the&nbsp;<em>y</em>-axis, which occurs at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. It’s given that the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 9 x plus 9\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></math>. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals minus 9 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis plus 9\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 9\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>. It follows that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 9\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and that the <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 0 comma 9 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. Therefore, the <em>y</em>-coordinate of the <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> in the <em>xy</em>-plane is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn></math>.</p>","externalid":"0beb2470-2acd-4279-917c-0e0172947d97","correct_answer":["9"]}}